description:
The Anka-team is pleased to announce the availability of:

Pisi Linux RC v1 (codename: Izmir)
* Kernel 3.10.12
* Firefox 24
* Libreoffice 4.1.1.2
* KDE 4.11.1
* Latest versions of lots of free software.
* Available in many languages (also for installation).
* For VirtualBox installation, the virtual disk must be at least 10 GB.

Download the ISO: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://packages.pisilinux.org/iso/rcv1/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://packages.pisilinux.org/iso/rcv1/&lt;/a&gt;

URL for the new - and persistent - package repository (included in RC ISO): &lt;a href=&quot;
http://packages.pisilinux.org/repositories/1.0/stable/x86_64/pisi-index....&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://packages.pisilinux.org/repositories/1.0/stable/x86_64/pisi-index....&lt;/a&gt;

While you can upgrade your Beta Sueno Installation, this is not recommended (we do not know which packages are installed on your system). To avoid problems, you are therefore advised to perform a fresh installation of Pisi Linux RC Izmir.

You may wish to discuss this release here at the forum: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://forum.pisilinuxworld.org/index.php?topic=278.0&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://forum.pisilinuxworld.org/index.php?topic=278.0&lt;/a&gt;

or, at the main Pisi Linux forum: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://forum.pisilinux.org/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://forum.pisilinux.org/&lt;/a&gt;

Finally, we (Anka Team) still need new developers, please contact us. Let's do it together! Thank you.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Please remember to use a slow writing speed when burning the ISO to optical media.

* Correct method (thanks Yoyo) for creating bootable USB device:

From the folder containing the downloaded ISO, enter the following via a Terminal Window ......

Code: sudo dd bs=4M if=Pisi-Linux-Rc1-izmir-v01.iso of=/dev/sdX

Replace 'X' to match your particular target USB drive, for example: sdb, sdc, etc ...

- See more at: http://pisilinuxworld.org/node/25#sthash.QZiDPMqG.dpuf
